theHarvester
Email and subdomain harvesting tool

Information Gathering
Description
theHarvester is an OSINT tool designed to gather email accounts, subdomain names, virtual hosts, open ports, banners, and employee names from different public sources like search engines.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which theHarvester
Install command:

sudo apt install theharvester
Basic Syntax
theHarvester -d <domain> -b <source>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
theHarvester -d target.com -b google

Google search	Basic email/subdomain harvesting	
theHarvester -d target.com -b all

All sources	Comprehensive OSINT gathering	
theHarvester -d target.com -b linkedin

LinkedIn search	Finding employee names	
theHarvester -d target.com -b bing -l 500

Limit results	Control number of results	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Choose target domain
2
Select data source (google, bing, linkedin, all)
3
Run theHarvester
4
Review emails, subdomains found
5
Use results for further reconnaissance
Understanding the Output
Output shows discovered emails, hostnames, IPs, and subdomains organized by source.

Important Warnings
•
This is passive reconnaissance - generally legal
•
Some API sources require keys
•
Respect rate limits of search engines
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
